---
import { Image } from "astro:assets";
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import printer from "../assets/printer.svg";
---

<BaseLayout
    title="MuISi Abiline - Label Printing for Collection Management Systems"
>
    <main>
        <section class="section section--yellow hero">
            <div class="container split split--hero">
                <div class="stack">
                    <h1>
                        Browser-based label printing for collection management
                        systems
                    </h1>

                    <p class="lead-xl">
                        <strong>MuISi Abiline</strong> is a browser extension that
                        enables direct label printing from Estonia's museum collection
                        management system (MuIS) without requiring additional software.
                    </p>
                    <p class="lead-xl">
                        Print one or a thousand labels with just a few clicks.
                    </p>
                </div>
                <div class="hero-media">
                    <Image
                        src={printer}
                        alt=""
                        width={215}
                        height={378}
                        priority
                    />
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="section">
            <div class="container">
                <div class="stack">
                    <h2>A universal approach</h2>

                    <p>
                        While MuISi Abiline was built specifically for the
                        Estonian museum information system,
                        <strong
                            >the same browser extension approach can be applied
                            to any collection management system</strong
                        >.
                    </p>

                    <h3>Two implementation paths</h3>

                    <div class="implementation-cards">
                        <div class="impl-card">
                            <h4>MuISi Abiline 2 (API-based)</h4>
                            <p>
                                <strong>Ideal approach:</strong> The collection management
                                system provides an API endpoint that returns structured
                                data about objects. The browser extension fetches
                                this data and formats it for label printing.
                            </p>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Clean separation of concerns</li>
                                <li>Reliable data extraction</li>
                                <li>Easy to maintain and update</li>
                                <li>
                                    Works with any label printer with ZPL
                                    support
                                </li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>

                        <div class="impl-card">
                            <h4>MuISi Abiline 1 (DOM-based)</h4>
                            <p>
                                <strong>Alternative approach:</strong> When no API
                                is available, the browser extension can extract data
                                directly from the webpage's HTML structure (DOM manipulation).
                            </p>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Works without system modifications</li>
                                <li>No backend changes required</li>
                                <li>May need updates when UI changes</li>
                                <li>Suitable for legacy systems</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <h3>Why barcodes?</h3>

                    <ul>
                        <li>
                            <strong>Faster object lookup and inventory</strong> -
                            Scan and find objects instantly instead of manual searching
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <strong
                                >Accelerate and error-proof digitization
                                workflows</strong
                            > - Reduce human error in data entry and speed up cataloging
                            processes
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <strong>Public-facing applications</strong> - Enable visitors
                            to scan barcodes/QR codes for additional information about
                            museum objects
                        </li>
                    </ul>

                    <h3>Key features</h3>

                    <ul>
                        <li>
                            <strong>Barcode scanning integration</strong> - Quick
                            object lookup using collection IDs
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <strong>Direct label printing</strong> - Print to thermal
                            label printers without intermediate software
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <strong>Batch operations</strong> - Print labels for multiple
                            objects at once
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <strong>Inventory acceleration</strong> - 20% faster object
                            verification in practice
                        </li>
                    </ul>

                    <div class="cta-section">
                        <h2>Interested in similar solution?</h2>
                        <p>
                            Whether your collection management system has an API
                            or not, a browser extension-based label printing
                            solution can streamline your museum's workflow.
                        </p>
                        <a href="mailto:hembo@ajapaik.ee" class="btn-cta"
                            >Get in touch</a
                        >
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>
    </main>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
    .implementation-cards {
        display: grid;
        gap: 2rem;
        margin: 2rem 0;
    }

    @media (min-width: 900px) {
        .implementation-cards {
            grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
        }
    }

    .impl-card {
        border: var(--ui-border);
        padding: 1.5rem;
        background: var(--white);
    }

    .impl-card h4 {
        margin-top: 0;
        color: var(--dark);
    }

    .impl-card ul {
        margin-top: 1rem;
    }

    .impl-card li {
        margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    }

    .cta-section {
        margin-top: 4rem;
        padding: 3rem;
        background: var(--yellow);
        border: var(--ui-border);
        text-align: center;
    }

    .cta-section h2 {
        margin-top: 0;
    }

    .btn-cta {
        display: inline-block;
        padding: 1rem 2rem;
        margin-top: 1.5rem;
        background: var(--dark);
        color: var(--white);
        text-decoration: none;
        border: var(--ui-border);
        font-weight: 700;
        font-size: 1.1rem;
        transition: transform 0.2s;
    }

    .btn-cta:hover {
        transform: translateY(-2px);
        text-decoration: none;
    }
</style>
